      "options": {
        "mode": "html",
        "code": { "language": "plaintext", "showLineNumbers": false, "showMiniMap": false },
        "content": "<div style=\"display:flex;gap:24px;align-items:flex-start;padding:4px 8px;\">\n  <img src=\"http://plant-pi.local:8088/plant-node-01.jpg\" style=\"width:220px;border-radius:8px;flex-shrink:0;object-fit:cover;\">\n  <div style=\"flex:1;min-width:0;\">\n    <h2 style=\"margin:0 0 4px 0;\">Rattlesnake plant</h2>\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 12px 0;opacity:0.85;\"><em>Goeppertia insignis</em> <span style=\"opacity:0.6;\">(formerly Calathea lancifolia)</span> &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; profile <strong>constant-moist</strong> &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; pot 1.5 L</p>\n    <h3 style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;\">Care</h3>\n    <ul style=\"margin:0 0 8px 0;padding-left:20px;line-height:1.5;\">\n      <li><strong>Water:</strong> NL tap water is fine (no chlorine, no fluoride, ~8 &deg;dH). Rainwater is a bonus, not required.</li>\n      <li><strong>Soil:</strong> keep moist, never fully dry; aim 50&ndash;75 % moisture</li>\n      <li><strong>Light:</strong> bright <em>indirect</em>, ideal band ~500&ndash;5000 lx; direct sun bleaches the leaves</li>\n      <li><strong>Humidity:</strong> matters most in winter (heaters on, ~30 %). Watch the leaves; pebble tray or away from radiators if tips start crisping again.</li>\n      <li><strong>Watering style:</strong> small frequent top-ups; never deep-flood</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p style=\"margin:0;opacity:0.65;font-size:0.9em;\"><em>Brown leaf-tips visible at intake are historical winter damage (dry indoor air during heating season). With heaters off for spring, new growth should come in clean.</em></p>\n  </div>\n</div>"
      },
